      • addAnalytic

        public SirqulResponse addAnalytic(String tag,
                         Long accountId,
                         String appKey,
                         AppVersion appVersion,
                         String device,
                         String deviceType,
                         String deviceOS,
                         String model,
                         Location location,
                         Long customId,
                         Long achievementIncrement,
                         String city,
                         String state,
                         String country,
                         String zip,
                         String locationDescription,
                         Long clientTime)
                           throws SirqulException
        Record an analytic record for a known state within the application.

        Target API Endpoint: /analytics/usage
        Parameters:
        tag - The tag to apply: the name of the action or thing being logged.
        accountId - The logged in user ID
        appKey - The application key unique to each application.
        appVersion - The current build version of the application
        device - The name of the device being used (iPhone5,1 , HTC Nexus One, x86_64, etc.)
        deviceType - The type of device (Handheld or Desktop)
        deviceOS - The operating system that the device is using (iPhone OS 5.0, Android OS 2.3.6, Windows 7 Service Pack 1, etc.)
        model - The model of the device (iPhone5,1 , Nexus One, etc.)
        location - the location
        customId - A customId used to associate the usage record with some other record in the system
        achievementIncrement - Determines how many achievement points and/or ranking points the user gets if this analytic is associated with an achievement
        city - The current city of the user
        state - The current state of the user
        country - The current country of the user
        zip - The current zip of the user
        locationDescription - The general description of the user's location
        clientTime - Timestamp sent from device
        Returns:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

                              String data)
                                throws SirqulException
        Sends multiple analytics.

        Target API Endpoint: /analytics/usage/batch
        Parameters:
        accountId - The account ID of the logged in user making the request
        appKey - The application key unique to each application.
        appVersion - The current build version of the application
        device - The device. If null, what was generated during Sirqul initialization is used.
        deviceType - The device type. If null, what was generated during Sirqul initialization is used.
        deviceOS - The device OS. If null, what was generated during Sirqul initialization is used.
        model - The device model. If null, what was generated during Sirqul initialization is used.
        data - The analytic data
        Returns:
        a SirqulResponse with a message of success or fail
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

      • createGriplyUrlWithAnalytics

        public String createGriplyUrlWithAnalytics(String griplyUrl,
                                  String appKey,
                                  Map<String,String> parameters)
                                    throws UnsupportedEncodingException
        Locally construct a griply url with analytics appended. This is a thread safe method and makes no network calls.
        Parameters:
        griplyUrl - the griply url to have values appended to
        appKey - the application key
        parameters - the parameters, where the keys are the parameters of the /analytics/usage api, and values are the values you'd like for each parameter.
        Returns:
        the string
        Throws:
        UnsupportedEncodingException - if a values cannot be encoded via URLEncoder with "UTF-8" charset.

      • getAnalyticsAggregatedFiltered

        public SirqulResponse getAnalyticsAggregatedFiltered(Long accountId,
                                            String appKey,
                                            Long startDate,
                                            Long endDate,
                                            String device,
                                            String deviceType,
                                            String deviceOS,
                                            String model,
                                            Enums.AudienceGender gender,
                                            Enums.AgeGroup ageGroup,
                                            String country,
                                            String state,
                                            String city,
                                            String zip,
                                            String tag,
                                            Long userAccountId,
                                            String userAccountDisplay,
                                            String userAccountUsername,
                                            Enums.AnalyticsApiMap groupByRoot,
                                            Enums.AnalyticsApiMap groupBy,
                                            Enums.AnalyticsApiMap distinctCount,
                                            Enums.AnalyticsApiMap sortField,
                                            Boolean descending,
                                            Boolean hideUnknown,
                                            Enums.ResponseFormat responseFormat,
                                            Integer limit,
                                            Location location)
                                              throws SirqulException
        Query analytics to get data used for nested graphs and charts.

        Target API Endpoint: /analytics/aggregatedFilteredUsage
        Parameters:
        accountId - The account id of the user (deviceId or accountId required, deviceId added automatically)
        appKey - The application key used to filter results by application
        startDate - Used to search for results after or equal to this date (UNIX time-stamp in milliseconds)
        endDate - Used to search for results before or equal to this date (UNIX time-stamp in milliseconds)
        device - The device to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        deviceType - The device type to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        deviceOS - The device OS to filter results by (performs a LIKE search)
        model - The model to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        gender - The gender to filter results by {MALE, FEMALE}
        ageGroup - Comma separated list of age groups to filter by {AGE_0_13, AGE_14_17, AGE_18_22, AGE_23_30, AGE_31_54, AGE_55_PLUS}
        country - The country to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        state - The state to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        city - The city to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        zip - The zip to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        tag - The tag to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        userAccountId - The account id to filter results for a particular user
        userAccountDisplay - The user display to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        userAccountUsername - The username to filter results by (performs a wild-card search)
        groupByRoot - Determines how to group results. For example, passing in 'CREATED' will return results by date. Passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return results by user {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, APPLICATION_NAME_BY_ID}
        groupBy - Determines how to group the nested data. {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, APPLICATION_NAME_BY_ID}
        distinctCount - Performs a unique query on the specified column. For example, passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return the number of unique users. {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID, NEW_ACCOUNT}
        sortField - Determines whether the results will be sorted by day or by number of hits {CREATED, TAG_COUNT}
        descending - Determines whether to return results in descending order
        hideUnknown - Determines whether to return data that has empty or unknown values
        responseFormat - Determines whether to return a JOSN or XML representation of the graph results
        limit - Used to limit results to get a cleaner graph. The results that gets filtered out will be combined
        location - the current location of the user
        Returns:
        String if responseFormat equals Enums.ResponseFormat.XML and ChartData if responseFormat equals any other Enums.ResponseFormat. On error, returns SirqulResponse with message.
        Throws:
        SirqulException - the SirqulException. A custom exception type specifically thrown by this Sirqul SDK.

Passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return results by user {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, DEVICE_ID, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID}
        distinctCount - Performs a unique query on the specified column. For example, passing in 'ACCOUNT' will return the number of unique users. {TAG, CUSTOM_ID, TOKEN, MODEL, DEVICE_TYPE, DEVICE, DEVICE_OS, DEVICE_ID, IP_ADDRESS, STATE, CITY, ZIP, COUNTRY, ACCOUNT, APPLICATION_ID}
        sortField - Determines whether the results will be sorted by day or by number of hits {CREATED, TAG_COUNT}
        descending - Determines whether to return results in descending order
        hideUnknown - Determines whether to return data that has empty or unknown values
        responseFormat - Determines whether to return a JOSN or XML representation of the graph results
        limit - Used to limit results to get a cleaner graph. The results that gets filtered out will be combined
        location - the current location of the user
        Returns:
